(346, 'Observing the Earth from space', 'Science', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p2LIAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Breaking free of the Earth\'s surface to look down from above is longer a mere dream. Sophisticated instruments flown on satellites produce streams of data that, when inserted into complex information processes, increase our knowledge of the Earth system. Satellites have now revealed the limits and p...', 'FR', 0, 3.5),
